title: England player ratings against Czech Republic: Who fought hard and who floundered in Prague?
text:
In a laboured Euro 2020 qualifier that ended in a 2-1 defeat for England against the Czech Republic, who can go home with their head held high and who will struggle to look Gareth Southgate in the eye for the rest of the international break? Look no further for the answers.

Jordan Pickford 6

Two box-office saves, one in each half. Absolutely fuming with his defenders for both goals which gave him little chance. Distribution adequate.

Kieran Trippier 6

Life in Spain has done him the power of good, but restored confidence could only do so much amid the chaos around him. Tidy nevertheless.

Michael Keane 4
